         <abstract id="aspace_8530c8bbe5b43878f6c832ca4d0b7c35">The materials consist of correspondence, diary excerpts, and autobiographical writings documenting the lives of Yale students. Includes an interview by Cam Carr Polk with Elizabeth Boyd Carr (wife of Louis B. Carr) concerning her husband's discovery of Frisbee.</abstract>
    
